thread.title: Port of Hamburg Shows Germany Is Vulnerable on China Trade

author: Daniel Michaels
title: Port of Hamburg Shows Germany Is Vulnerable on China Trade
text:
HAMBURG, Germany—At a Chinese business summit here last fall, local officials boasted that this port city was “consolidating its position as China’s gateway to European trade.” Today that position offers less to brag about.
China is by far the biggest trading partner for Hamburg, the largest port in the world’s fourth-biggest economy. Last year one of every three containers in Hamburg harbor was coming from or heading to China.
